.TH "snd_card_disconnect_sync" 9 "snd_card_disconnect_sync" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_card_disconnect_sync \- disconnect card and wait until files get closed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_card_disconnect_sync
.BI "(struct snd_card *card "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
card object to disconnect
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This calls \fBsnd_card_disconnect\fP for disconnecting all belonging components
and waits until all pending files get closed.
It assures that all accesses from user-space finished so that the driver
can release its resources gracefully.
